# PRD Verification Complete - 2026-04-19

## Verification Summary

All PRD v1.0 requirements verified as SATISFIED on 2026-04-19.

### Functional Requirements (FR-01 to FR-24) - ALL SATISFIED
- FR-01 to FR-04: Job submission, queue polling, priority ordering, concurrent job limiting
- FR-05 to FR-09: Training execution, mixed precision, checkpoints, sample generation
- FR-10 to FR-12: Dataset management, validation, preprocessing
- FR-13 to FR-16: Control files (.pause, .cancel, .done, .lock)
- FR-17 to FR-20: Logging, auditability, notifications
- FR-21 to FR-24: GPU management, VRAM monitoring, OOM recovery, temperature monitoring

### Non-Functional Requirements (NFR-01 to NFR-06) - ALL SATISFIED
- NFR-01: Reproducibility (deterministic seeding, CUBLAS workspace config)
- NFR-02: Portability (Docker + NVIDIA Container Toolkit)
- NFR-03: Startup Time (< 120s cold start)
- NFR-04: Fault Tolerance (state recovery, graceful shutdown)
- NFR-05: Security (air-gap compatible, no telemetry)
- NFR-06: Observability (SQLite + log file queryable without exec)

### Infrastructure - ALL SATISFIED
- Dockerfile with nvidia/cuda:12.4.1-runtime-ubuntu22.04 base
- ENTRYPOINT to orchestrator.sh
- VOLUME /data for persistent state
- HEALTHCHECK via healthcheck.sh
- Environment variables per Section 9.2
- docker-compose.yml with GPU passthrough

### Orchestrator Design - ALL SATISFIED
- Single-loop Bash architecture
- Job lifecycle state machine
- Signal handling (SIGTERM, SIGINT)
- Stale lock detection (300s timeout)
- Heartbeat mechanism

### SQLite Schema - ALL SATISFIED
- runs, metrics, events tables per Appendix B
- All required columns and indexes
- WAL mode enabled

